Installation steps
- install tomcat version 8
- pull or unpack payourshare-server.war
- modify the server.xml:
    1. Change the root path of the project in line 133 to:
        <Context docBase="payourshare-server" path="/server" reloadable="true" source="org.eclipse.jst.jee.server:payourshare-server"/></Host>
    2. Change the path for the keystore in line 84 so that it points to your keystore:
        keystoreFile="/path/to/your/keystore/key-server"
        
        if you use your own keys you should also change the pass in line 85 according to your setup
        (for additional info look here: http://www.mkyong.com/tomcat/how-to-configure-tomcat-to-support-ssl-or-https/)
- create a database user "payourshare" or modify /payourshare-server/src/entities/SQLNames.java
- import the sql schema (payourshare-cleaned.sql) for your user
- rebuild if necessary
- run it!